'''Klajdi Kuka''' (born 29 March 1989) is an [[Albanians|Albanian]] [[Association football|footballer]]. He currently plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[KF Tirana]] in the [[Albanian Superliga]].
==Career== Kuka is with [[KF Tirana]] only as an apprentice and is currently their 3rd choice goalkeeper behing the legendary [[Albanians|Albanian]] veteran [[Blendi Nallbani]] and [[Macedonia (country)|Macedonian]] [[Pece Korunovski]].<ref>[http://playerhistory.com/Default.aspx?page=player_details&playerID=200386 Playerhistory.com Profile]</ref> He made his debut for [[KF Tirana]] at the age of 18 on the last day of the 2007-2008 season against [[KS Kastrioti Kruje]]. The match was played on 17 May 2008 and Kuka started the game and played the full 90 minutes.<ref>[http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.match.kastrioti-kruje.kf-tirana.255654.en.html Kuka debut]</ref> The young goalkeeper has failed to make another appearance for the club. Now he plays for [[KS Tomori Berat]]
